  {
    "number": 1,
    "title": "Usapyon is Here!",
    "overview": "Hailey Anne Thomas, a space fanatic around Nate's age, purchases a Space Watch (actually a Yo-kai Watch Model U prototype) from her local anime shop. Using the watch, she meets Usapyon, whom she first thinks is an alien, but is disappointed to learn he's a Yo-kai. Usapyon explains to Hailey Anne his predicament involving his former master, a rocket engineer at NASA",
    "air_date": "2015-07-10",
    "still": "https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/yR9fH7QHusbN0fGvMbJ5C7PCEtR.jpg",
    "runtime": 22,
    "vote_average": 0,
    "tmdb_id": 1311659
  },
  {
    "number": 2,
    "title": "Episode 2",
    "overview": "Nate receives the new Yo-kai Watch Model U prototype, but the Yo-kai Cornfused makes him unimpressed with the new features. Meanwhile, Hailey Anne and Usapyon start on a weekly-magazine rocket project to help the latter's old master rediscover his dreams.",
    "air_date": "2015-07-17",
    "still": "https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/9zUgrLenUm0Wy3FEsuVhSHYDDYJ.jpg",
    "runtime": 22,
    "vote_average": 0,
    "tmdb_id": 1311660
  },
  {
    "number": 3,
    "title": "Episode 3",
    "overview": "Komasan hears about a masseur with the \"hands of a god\" and decides to go see him. But the masseur is surprised that he can't find Komasan's tense spot. Meanwhile, Nate and his friends try to have fun at the beach, but the day is plagued by the Yo-kai Roughraff, Swosh, and others.",
    "air_date": "2015-07-24",
    "still": "https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/vHX27XnYwfT7QEtzuL3AiVHWLTX.jpg",
    "runtime": 22,
    "vote_average": 0,
